title: Foreign Policy | Fox News
description: Stay connected with the latest Foreign Policy news and highlights from around the world with Fox News. Get up-to-the-minute coverage, expert analysis, and updates regarding foreign policy.

Elon Musk was seen at a White House dinner for Saudi Crown Prince Mohammed bin Salman.

Dr. Qanta Ahmed, senior fellow at the Independent Women's Forum and Council on Foreign Relations member, analyzes the historical significance of the U.S.-Saudi relationship and its critical role for the region.

Panelists Jayme Leagh Franklin and Caroline Sunshine discuss the Trump administration's plans to dismantle the Department of Education and the meeting between President Donald Trump and Saudi Crown Prince Mohammed Bin Salman on 'Fox News @ Night.'
Trump designated Saudi Arabia a major non-NATO ally during a historic White House dinner with Crown Prince Mohammed bin Salman, marking 80 years of relations.
Sen. Ted Cruz, R-Texas., comments on Trump’s foreign policy agenda while he hosts the crown prince of Saudi Arabia on ‘Jesse Watters Primetime.’
An ‘All-star’ panel discusses the long-term impact of the Epstein files and the potential of normalization between Israel and Saudi Arabia on ‘Special Report.’

Fox News correspondent David Spunt reports on President Donald Trump’s meeting with Saudi Crown Prince Mohammed bin Salman, where the two discussed military cooperation, and the crown prince faced questions about Saudi Arabia’s alleged ties to the 9/
The Trump administration provides a $1 billion loan to Constellation Energy to restart the Three Mile Island nuclear reactor, potentially powering 800,000 homes.
President Donald Trump and Saudi Arabia's Crown Prince Mohammed bin Salman take questions from reporters as they work to negotiate terms for the Abraham Accords, F-35 fighter jets and more.
Harvard Belfer Center senior fellow Karen Elliott House joins 'Fox & Friends' to discuss President Donald Trump's White House meeting with Saudi Crown Prince Mohammed bin Salman.
FDD research analyst Mariam Wahba discusses Nicki Minaj's advocacy for persecuted Christians in Nigeria as the rapper is set to speak alongside United Nations Ambassador Mike Waltz.
Ahead of the Saudi crown prince’s visit to Washington, 9/11 survivors and victims’ families are demanding Trump press Saudi Arabia over its alleged role in the 2001 attacks.
Mohammed bin Salman returns to White House for first time since 2018 as Trump hosts formal ceremony and bilateral meetings with Saudi leader.
Marco Rubio confirms the Cartel de los Soles designation under Section 219, citing the group's corruption of Venezuelan institutions and drug trafficking.
President Donald Trump speaks with reporters at Palm Beach International Airport about the Jeffrey Epstein files, negotiating with lawmakers about healthcare and more.
Venezuelan President Nicolás Maduro referenced the late Beatles icon during a rally as U.S. warships patrol nearby Caribbean waters, a move Washington says targets drug trafficking. (Credit: AP)
U.S. Treasury Secretary Scott Bessent joins 'Sunday Morning Futures' to discuss talks with China over rare earth materials, the legality of Trump's tariffs, the affordability crisis and more.
'The Age of Disclosure' director and producer Dan Farah discusses his upcoming documentary about an alleged 80-year coverup of non-human intelligent life and addresses skepticism on 'Special Report.'
The State Department has designated four Antifa-linked groups operating in Europe as foreign terrorist organizations. Foreign threats expert Ryan Mauro offers insight on 'Fox & Friends.'
Ken Isaacs analyzes the shift from "famine" to "starvation" terminology in Gaza coverage, questioning whether technical data supported the humanitarian crisis claims.
After 13 people were killed in bear attacks, the U.S. is warning Americans in Japan to stay alert and avoid areas where bears have been seen.
Vice President JD Vance shares the lessons he has learned from President Donald Trump during an exclusive interview with 'Hannity.'
Hillary Clinton and Mike Pompeo find rare common ground, rejecting Pentagon's spheres of influence strategy that could benefit China and Russia globally.
State Department makes historic move designating four European Antifa groups as foreign terrorist organizations for first time in U.S. history.
Iran claims missile capacity now exceeds pre-war levels after June bombardment of nuclear facilities by Israel and U.S. during 12-Day War conflict.
IOC prepares to ban transgender women from female Olympic events following scientific review showing permanent male physical advantages in sports competition.
U.S. embassies have received guidance to consider denying visas to overweight applicants and those with chronic health conditions, citing potential financial costs to American taxpayers.
Fox News' Gillian Turner reports on a 'seismic shift' after Syria's new leader, Ahmed Al-Sharaa, meets with President Donald Trump in a historic White House visit.
Syrian President Ahmed al-Sharaa explains how his country is a 'geopolitical ally' with the U.S., addresses his past connections to al-Qaeda and more on 'Special Report.'
President Donald Trump takes questions from the press after the swearing-in ceremony for U.S. Ambassador to India Sergio Gor at the Oval Office.
